summary:
I embarked on my journey in app development six years ago, initially delving into Ionic framework during an internship. Subsequently, I ventured into Java for Android app development, honing my skills in text processing from images.

Following a friend's recommendation, I transitioned to Flutter, Google's latest offering, and explored its nascent developer community. As I immersed myself in Flutter, I undertook diverse app projects, encountering challenges ranging from authentication services to notification handling and server integration.

I also ventured into specialized tasks, such as crafting music players, chat applications, and even an Augmented Reality system that places three-dimensional images onto surfaces, providing image outputs from this environment.

Throughout this journey, I assimilated various architectural paradigms, with Test-Driven Development (TDD) and Model-View-Controller (MVC) being my steadfast allies. I seamlessly integrated some of the most renowned state management solutions, achieving mastery in Bloc, GetX, and provider.

With a portfolio of eleven applications, each excelling in distinct domains, some already in the public domain and others on the cusp of release, I stand poised to take on new challenges in mobile app development.

position.title: Senior Flutter Developer
position.description:
• Spearheaded the application development team, responsible for identifying the best solutions and plugins.
• Implemented initial project setups and widget componentization.
• Utilized BLoC for effective state management and integrated dependencies with the Get_it plugin.
• Achieved a 50% speed increase in application response times by implementing GraphQL in APIs for quicker access to server-side resources and information.

position.title: Senior Flutter Developer
position.location: North Sydney, New South Wales, Australia
position.description:
• Planned the progress of the app development project and divided the tasks of the app development team
• Assisted the Back-End development team in designing the data of the models submitted to the app
• Utilized uni_link plugin to manage links sent through notifications, seamlessly directing users to the relevant pages.
• Implemented url_launcher plugin for displaying web pages based on user tokens within the application.
• Updated the chat interface through Firebase notifications, providing a real-time stream of chat messages.

position.title: Flutter Developer
position.description:
• Designed, programmed, reviewed and unit test using flutter framework, dart, java Script, etc.
• Worked with other internal software development teams on integration engineering
• Troubleshot applications, identified bottlenecks and bugs, and devised solutions to mitigate and address issues.
• Developed mobile application based on MVC architecture
• Optimized product codes on “Get X State Management” which increased software performance by 30%

position.title: Co-Founder & Flutter Developer

• Joined the R&D team to find market needs and come up with ideas to solve problems
